            <article>
                <h1 itemprop="headline">Top CRM Startups in Paris in 2023</h1>
                <ol>
                    <li>Aircall<br/>Aircall is the phone system for modern business. An entirely cloud-based voice platform that integrates seamlessly with popular productivity and helpdesk tools that workplaces are already using, Aircall was built to make phone support as easy to manage as any other business workflow—accessible, transparent, and collaborative. Aircall believes that voice is the most powerful way to communicate with customers, prospects, candidates, and colleagues, and it is designed to take the headache out of what should be a delightful moment of human connection. Aircall was founded in 2014 and has raised over $100 million. Based in New York and Paris, the company has over 300 employees.</li>
                    <li>Surfe (ex-Leadjet)<br/>Surfe is on a mission to create the next generation sales productivity tool, aleviating the pains of daily work for the whole modern revenue team. We power sales through a flexible interface that makes CRM accessible everywhere. We connect the CRM to additional data sources, resulting in less admin and more sales.</li>
                    <li>Agorapulse<br/>More than an award-winning social media management tool, Agorapulse is a complete solution that makes the entire experience of managing social easier and more enjoyable for you. - Improved Engagement: Capture all messages across your social media profiles. No more missing messages! - Painless Publishing: Schedule posts, queue posts, categorize queued posts, bulk posts, and delete posts—all with less hassles and headaches. - Clear, Powerful Reporting: Get deep social media metrics in far less time and with greater clarity. - Always on Marketing: Be alerted to social media trends, hashtags, and relevant content, and avoid spam and newsfeed clutters. Our mission is to make our users feel like they are the only one in the room when they need us. Our team continuously achieves a 95% Happiness Score and a first-response time far faster than our competitors’ seven hours. It's why we’re rated #1 in social media management software and social media marketing software by Capterra, the No. 1 software reviews provider.</li>
                    <li>Pimster<br/>We provide brands with a SaaS platform to build digital product-guides.</li>
                    <li>Modjo.ai<br/>Rather than rely on data that is manually typed into their CRM, 1/ Modjo captures from the source : emails, phone calls and video calls. 2/ Using Natural Language Understanding to analyze and detect insights for the customer facing people and leadership, product and marketing teams. The 3 main value propositions are 1/ Performances improvement : Increase your conversion rates from 25%, divide by 3 the onboarding time for new reps and reduce from 37% your sales cycle. 2/ Insights into your pipeline : By capturing every interactions Modjo proactively brings your attention to risks in your pipeline before the deal is lost. 3/ Visibility into your Market : Hear the need of your customers, what they say about your new features or competitors</li>
                    <li>Diduenjoy<br/>DIDUENJOY uses NPS, eNPs, CSAT, CES to gather feedback from your customers and employees at every point of their journey. Over 100% growth per year (since its creation in 2014). No fundraising, no debt: a profitable business. Offices at Bonne Nouvelle (Paris 10th district) in a beautiful loft.</li>
                    <li>Arenametrix<br/>In the context of ticketing innovation, Tech'4'Team is developing innovative technology solutions for sports, cultural and recreational infrastructures. Tech'4'Team offers are technological tools known as ARENAMETRIX: a Yield Management turnkey solution, flexible and integrated for ticketing to offer "fair" price tickets to the audience. </li>
                    <li>LineUp7</li>
                </ol>
